<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="35" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="35">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="35">
Morphological and phylogenetic data supported placement of this isolate as 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Botryosphaeriaceae" genus="Lasiodiplodia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lasiodiplodia theobromae" order="Botryosphaeriales" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="theobromae">Lasiodiplodia theobromae</taxonomicName>
. The phylogenetic analysis showed the isolate groups with 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Botryosphaeriaceae" genus="Lasiodiplodia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lasiodiplodia theobromae" order="Botryosphaeriales" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="theobromae">Lasiodiplodia theobromae</taxonomicName>
. Nucleotide base pairs of published sequences of 
<taxonomicName class="Dothideomycetes" family="Botryosphaeriaceae" genus="Lasiodiplodia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lasiodiplodia theobromae" order="Botryosphaeriales" pageId="10" pageNumber="35" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="theobromae">Lasiodiplodia theobromae</taxonomicName>
(strain EucN188, CBS 111530, PHLO9, CDFA145) were also compared with the sequence and found that the nucleotide base pairs of the ITS gene are 100% similar.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
